	<strong>US CPSC Issues Draft Rulemaking Notice for Determining the Exemption of Certain Untreated and Unfinished Engineered Wood Products</strong>
	<p>On September 27, 2017, the Consumer Product Safety Commission (CPSC) issued a <a href="https://www.cpsc.gov/content/ballot-vote-draft-notice-of-proposed-rulemaking-children%E2%80%99s-products-children%E2%80%99s-toys-and" target="_blank">draft rulemaking notice</a> to determine that certain untreated and unfinished engineered wood products would not contain harmful chemicals that are limited under CPSIA and ASTM F963.</p>
	<a href="/regulatory-updates/October-2017/oct2017-us-cpsc-exempt-wood" class="recapViewStory" style="float:right;">View Story</a>
	<a href="javascript://" class="learnmore" style="float:left;">Read More</a>
	<div style="clear:both;"></div>
	<div class="moretext">
		<p>Upon approval, the following three untreated and unfinished engineered wood products, which are made from virgin wood or pre-consumer waste wood, would be exempted from third party testing for compliance with the requirements of CPSIA lead, CPSIA phthalates and ASTM F963 heavy elements in children’s products, children’s toys and child care articles: </p>
		<ol>
			<li>Particleboard</li>
			<li>Hardwood plywood</li>
			<li>Medium Density fiberboard</li>
		</ol>
	</div><br />
</div>

