	<strong>EU CEN Amends EN 71-3 Related to Migration of Certain Elements</strong>
	<p>In August 2017, the European Committee for Standardization (CEN) published a new amendment to toys safety standard for migration of certain elements, EN 71-3:2013+A2:2017. The amended standard supersedes EN 71-3:2013+A1:2014.</p>
	<a href="/regulatory-updates/October-2017/oct2017-cen-amends-en71-3" class="recapViewStory" style="float:right;">View Story</a>
	<a href="javascript://" class="learnmore" style="float:left;">Read More</a>
	<div style="clear:both;"></div>
	<div class="moretext">
		<p>In the amended standard, EN 71-3:2013+A2:2017, the key changes are summarized below:</p>
		<ol>
			<li>Updated test methods for detection of organic tin</li>
			<li>Added organic tin confirmation method: ISO/TS 16179</li>
		</ol>
		<p>Upon harmonisation to Toys Safety Directive 2009/48/EC, the standard will become mandatory.</p>
	</div><br />
</div>

